               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary"> The <title>Tuḥfat al-Ḥabīb</title> (Gift of the
                     Friend), a alphabetically arranged anthology of <hi rend="italic">ghazal</hi>
                     lyric poems from the 13th to early 16th centuries CE. Compiled by Safavid-era
                     poet Fakhrī Haravī (ca. 1497–1566), pen-named <addName type="penname"
                        >Amīrī</addName>, he dedicated it to his patron, then-governor of Herat,
                     <persName role="dte" key="person_f7917">Karīm al-Dīn Khvājah Ḥabīb Allāh Savājī</persName>.
                     (fl. early 16th c). Albeit undated, this finely copied manuscript bears a
                     illuminated header and appears likely completed in the Mughal empire.</summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_864-item1">
                     <author key="person_66081639" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66081639/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Fakhrī Haravī, Sultān
